# VSTO Add-in — register every new `.cs` file

`src/DocuLink.Addin/DocuLink.Addin.csproj` uses **explicit** `<Compile Include="..."/>` items. New files under `src/DocuLink.Addin/` are **not** picked up automatically (unlike SDK-style projects).

## When you add or move a `.cs` file

1. Open `DocuLink.Addin.csproj`.
2. Add a sibling-style entry under the existing `<Compile Include="Modules\..."/>` blocks, e.g.  
   `<Compile Include="Modules\Services\YourNewService.cs" />`
3. If the file is a form/control, match the pattern used for `TaskPaneHost.cs` (`SubType`, etc.).

## Symptom if you skip this

`The type or namespace name 'X' could not be found` even though the file exists — the type was never compiled into the assembly.

## Quick checklist

- [ ] New or moved `.cs` under `DocuLink.Addin` has a matching `<Compile Include=...>` in `DocuLink.Addin.csproj`.
